            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I'm not sure whether this needs to be ported back to VIm, since the issue doesn't reproduce there. Vim also treats `~` as a special character and converts `ADMINI~1` to `^ADMINI\\~1$`, but it later enumerates directories using `FindFirstFileW`. That allows it to match both long names and fall back to short names.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/vim/vim/blob/3cc8c393030d8fdae75bdbb431cca09234a76479/src/filepath.c#L3713-L3715",
            "commit_id": "7ef60204f162363a676092dd156908d7971b1a22",
            "created_at": "2026-06-09T04:03:40Z",
