        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I updated the Problem/Solution. For future reference:\r\n\r\nWhen framing the Problem/Solution, the most important info is \"why\". https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/25019 gives a very good answer to that, but it's missing here.\r\n\r\n`vim.fn.stdpath() can return unsupported 8.3 DOS filenames` is the actual problem, but is not mentioned here.\r\n\r\nAlso we don't support DOS filenames, so the next question is why we care, which is answered by the first item in that issue:\r\n\r\n> Windows will truncate some long usernames into `6ch~N` names.\r\n\r\nAnother important callout:\r\n\r\n> This effect is **only** observed when running nvim under `cmd.exe`\r\n\r\nYour [comment](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/25019#issuecomment-4639582178) also has good notes.\r\n",
            "created_at": "2026-06-10T10:38:49Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/40144#issuecomment-4669229764",
            "id": 4669229764,
